---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const _b = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const base = _b.endsWith('/') ? _b : _b + '/';
---
<Layout title="About — Expert Technology Consulting for Startups and SMBs" description="Solo technology expert helping startups and SMBs build secure, reliable systems. Direct access to a senior engineer. No big agency bloat.">
  <section class="section" style="text-align:center;padding:var(--space-16) 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">About</span>
      <h1 class="section-title" style="margin: 0 auto var(--space-6); font-size: var(--text-4xl);">Strategic Systems Engineering.<br /><span class="text-accent">No big agency bloat.</span></h1>
      <p style="max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto var(--space-8); font-size: var(--text-lg);">
        TurinTech Solutions is a specialized technical consultancy focused on IT modernization, identity governance, and automated systems architecture.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 800px;">
      <h2>Our Approach</h2>
      <p>
        We partner with organizations to bridge the gap between traditional IT infrastructure and modern, AI-enabled operational workflows. By enforcing strict security controls, rigorous documentation, and intelligent automation, we build environments that allow businesses to operate with absolute clarity and minimal friction.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every engagement is led by a senior systems engineer — not a junior account manager. You get direct access to the person designing and building your architecture. No layers of abstraction, no handoffs between departments, no billing by the hour for on-the-job learning.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 800px;">
      <h2>What We Believe</h2>
      <div class="values-grid" style="display: grid; gap: var(--space-6); margin-top: var(--space-6);">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Truth Over Comfort</h3>
          <p class="card-text">We tell you what your infrastructure actually needs, not what you want to hear. Sugar-coating technical reality is a disservice to your business.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Clarity Over Cleverness</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Every architecture should be obvious in retrospect. If a system requires a 45-minute whiteboard session to explain, it is overengineered.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Operational Reality</h3>
          <p class="card-text">We design for failure before success. A solution that works at 2 AM when monitoring is screaming is worth a hundred that look perfect in a diagram.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Utility Over Dogma</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Tools are replaceable; architectures are not. We use the right tool for the job, not the fashionable one, not the one on your preferred stack.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 800px;">
      <h2>Background</h2>
      <p>
        Founded by a senior engineer with 15+ years of production experience across systems architecture, game development, and autonomous infrastructure, TurinTech Solutions was built from the conviction that most organizations do not need an army of consultants — they need one person who understands the full stack and can execute without handholding.
      </p>
      <p>
        We have shipped software used by millions, debugged kernel panics at 3 AM, and learned the hard way that elegance without operational reality is academic vanity. Every engagement benefits from that experience — the shortcuts we learned not to take, the failure modes we learned to expect, and the architectures that actually survive contact with production.
      </p>
      <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: var(--space-12);">
        <a href="/#contact-form-section" class="btn btn-primary">Schedule a Technical Assessment</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .values-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .values-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
